<TITLE> Ex-adviser's son Afzal Hossain Raj jailed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court sent Dr Afzal Hossain Raj, son of a former caretaker government adviser, to jail, following his surrender in a corruption case on Sunday. Special judge ANM Bashirullah's court refused Raj bail, in the case filed last year under the Fakhruddin Ahmed-led caretaker government, said his lawyer Md Azizur Rahman Chowdhury. The case accuses Raj of transferring officials and staff of environment and law ministries without proper authority. He is also charged with making illegal bank transactions amounting to Tk 10.61 crore between Dec 2006 to Dec 2007, and illegally earning Tk 1.4 crore during the same period. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case with Ramna police on Sep 14 last year and and pressed charges on June 4 this year. Raj is the son of Fazlul Haque, who was an adviser to the forest, ministry of the Iajuddin Ahmed led caretaker government. Judge Bashirullah set charge framing in the case for later Sunday, but then deferred the hearing until Aug 4 and transferred the case to Special Judge's Court-1. bdnew
